1 (c) an identification of and commitment to implement specific mental health promotion activities;
2 (d) plans to develop a program management team, including representatives from the groups
3 listed under subsection (2)(b); and
4 (e) plans to evaluate the effectiveness of the program using specific metrics and establishing a
5 baseline for those metrics prior to implementing mental health promotion activities under the program.
6 (3) (a) Contingent on and within appropriations for the program, the office of public instruction shall
7 award grants to school districts displaying the greatest need, preparation, and promise of successfully
8 implementing mental health promotion activities under the program. If possible, the office of public instruction
9 shall award grants to districts in a manner that ensures diversity of district size and geography.
10 (b) The office of public instruction shall award annual grants to school districts of not less than
11 $10,000 or more than the lesser of an amount equal to $25 for each enrolled student in a participating school in
12 the prior school year or $50,000 in an amount that is not less than $5,000 and is not more than the lesser of:
13 (i) $25 for each student enrolled in a participating school in the prior school year; or
14 (ii) $50,000.
15 (c) A school district awarded a grant must receive the grant for 2 years and may reapply for a
16 second 2-year grant cycle.
17 (d) A school district receiving a grant under the program shall deposit the grant funds in the
18 district's miscellaneous programs fund and use the grant funds only for the costs of implementing mental health
19 promotion activities.
20 (4) (a) A school district receiving a grant under the program shall report to the office of public
21 instruction by July 15 of even numbered years. The report must include the following:
22 (i) an accounting of expenditures of grant funds;
23 (ii) a summary of mental health promotion activities implemented under the grant; and
24 (iii) an evaluation of the effectiveness of the grant in improving the mental health of students in
25 participating schools, including, if possible, the specific metrics under subsection (2)(e).
26 (b) The office of public instruction shall report, in accordance with 5-11-210, to the education
27 interim committee a compilation of the reports received under subsection (4)(a) and an agency evaluation of the
28 implementation of the program.
